{"type":"assistant.message","data":{"messageId":"bd15aedc-d46d-4c76-80cc-b8bc56751897","content":"Yes, you will hit compatibility issues. Here's the breakdown:\n\n**Framework support dropped in MSTest v3:**\n\n| Target | MSTest v3 Support |\n|---|---|\n| `net462` | ✅ Supported |\n| `net5.0` | ❌ Dropped (minimum is `net6.0`) |\n| `netcoreapp3.1` | ❌ Dropped (minimum is `net6.0`) |\n\nMSTest v3 requires **.NET 6+** for .NET (Core) targets. Both `net5.0` and `netcoreapp3.1` are end-of-life and no longer supported.\n\n**To migrate, you'd need to:**\n\n1. **Update target frameworks** — replace `net5.0` and `netcoreapp3.1` with supported versions (e.g., `net6.0`, `net8.0`).\n2. **Simplify package references** — MSTest v3 offers a single `MSTest` meta-package replacing the separate `MSTest.TestFramework` and `MSTest.TestAdapter` packages.\n\nWould you like me to update the project file for MSTest v3?","toolRequests":[],"interactionId":"349a17ff-4598-4d5f-87cb-6a3601d8e708","reasoningOpaque":"","reasoningText":"The user's project targets `net5.0`, `net462`, and `netcoreapp3.1`. MSTest v3 has dropped support for some older frameworks. Let me provide accurate information about compatibility issues.\n\nMSTest v3 key changes:\n- Minimum supported frameworks: .NET 6+ and .NET Framework 4.6.2+\n- `net5.0` is NOT supported (it's end-of-life; MSTest v3 requires .NET 6+)\n- `netcoreapp3.1` is NOT supported (end-of-life; MSTest v3 requires .NET 6+)\n\n\n- `net462` should still work since MSTest v3 supports .NET Framework 4.6.2+\n\nThe upgrade also consolidates the package structure—MSTest v3 uses a single `MSTest` meta-package instead of requiring separate `MSTest.TestFramework` and `MSTest.TestAdapter` references.","outputTokens":517,"requestId":"582C:3A51EB:15CE32C:172F58C:6A04605A"},"id":"c2870404-4cde-4782-bf2d-e5c5d1ab5cf2","timestamp":"2026-05-13T11:28:38.317Z","parentId":"76641e0c-adf4-4633-8f96-9053b498bc9f"}
